{"title_page": "C. R. Neelakandan", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2016}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=August 2016}}\n\n'''C. R. Neelakandan''' is an Indian environmental activist, politician and writer.<ref name=\"Social workers urged to work for the voiceless people\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-kerala/social-workers-urged-to-work-for-the-voiceless-people/article3086056.ece |title=Social workers urged to work for the voiceless people |date=2006-08-06 |website=The Hindu |language=en-IN |access-date=2018-11-07}}</ref> A a regular contributor to Malayalam periodicals on environmental issues, Neelakandan is the State Convener of [[Aam Aadmi Party]] Kerala since 3 January 2016.<ref name=\"CR Neelakandan \u2013 Aam Aadmi Party\">{{Cite web |url=http://kerala.aamaadmiparty.org/teams/cr-neelakandan/ |title=CR Neelakandan \u2013 Aam Aadmi Party |website=kerala.aamaadmiparty.org |language=en-US |access-date=2018-11-07}}</ref>\n\n== Biography ==\nNeelakandan born to C.P Raman Namboothiri and Savithri Antharjanam on 1957 at karuvannoor in Thrissur District, Kerala. He completed his education from Christ College Irinjalakkuda and [[Government Engineering College, Thrissur]]. He was an activist of [[Students' Federation of India|SFI]] at district and state level while studying. After his study he went on training from [[Bhabha Atomic Research Centre]] Bombay. He joined [[Keltron]] in 1981 and was the Deputy General Manager of Keltron in its Aroor branch and retired in May 2015.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.mathrubhumi.com/english/news.php?id=20823&cat=1&sub=14&subit=0 |title=Mathrubhumi - Keltron relocates CR Neelakandan |access-date=4 June 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120910045216/http://www.mathrubhumi.com/english/news.php?id=20823&cat=1&sub=14&subit=0 |archive-date=10 September 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nHe Began his political activism in students movement, he was arrested during [[The Emergency (India)|The Emergency]] and was held in illegal custody for alleged possession of communist literature. Later he joined SFI, and also worked in the Communist Party. In 2014, he joined the Aam Admi Party and became a member of the State Executive Committee. He actively participates in environmental issues such as public protest against waste dumping at various places across the state such as Lalur, Vilappilashala, Panamkuttichira, Brahmapuram, Pettippalam etc., Struggles like [[Silent Valley National Park|Silent Valley]], National Highway Protection Samithy, Chengara, [[Plachimada]], GAIUL Pipe Line, High Speed Rail Corridor, Many mining projects like Mineral sand mining on Arattupuzha Coast, Moolampilly displacement, Malabar Gold pollution, Periyar River Protection, [[Endosulfan]] in [[Kazaragod]], Aranmula Airport, Athirappilly and Pooyamkutty HEPs and many others.<ref name=\"\u0d2a\u0d4a\u0d2e\u0d4d\u0d2a\u0d3f\u0d33\u0d48 \u0d12\u0d30\u0d41\u0d2e\u0d48 \u0d2a\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d35\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d15\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d4d \u0d2a\u0d3f\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d41\u0d23: \u0d38\u0d3f.\u0d06\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d \u0d28\u0d40\u0d32\u0d15\u0d23\u0d4d\u0d20\u0d28\u0d4d\u200d  \u0d28\u0d3f\u0d30\u0d3e\u0d39\u0d3e\u0d30 \u0d38\u0d2e\u0d30\u0d02 \u0d24\u0d41\u0d1f\u0d19\u0d4d\u0d19\u0d3f\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.mathrubhumi.com/tv/ReadMore/34424/cr/E |title=\u0d2a\u0d4a\u0d2e\u0d4d\u0d2a\u0d3f\u0d33\u0d48 \u0d12\u0d30\u0d41\u0d2e\u0d48 \u0d2a\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d35\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d15\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d4d \u0d2a\u0d3f\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d41\u0d23: \u0d38\u0d3f.\u0d06\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d \u0d28\u0d40\u0d32\u0d15\u0d23\u0d4d\u0d20\u0d28\u0d4d\u200d  \u0d28\u0d3f\u0d30\u0d3e\u0d39\u0d3e\u0d30 \u0d38\u0d2e\u0d30\u0d02 \u0d24\u0d41\u0d1f\u0d19\u0d4d\u0d19\u0d3f |date=2018-11-07 |website=www.mathrubhumi.com |language=en |access-date=2018-11-07}}</ref><ref name=\"Making a Show: The Black Money Bill\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.epw.in/author/c-r-neelakandan |title=Making a Show: The Black Money Bill |date=2015-06-05 |website=Economic and Political Weekly |language=en |access-date=2018-11-07}}</ref><ref name=\"Govt Denying Freedom of Speech: C R Neelakandan\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.newsexperts.in/govt-denying-freedom-speech-c-r-neelakandam/ |title=Govt Denying Freedom of Speech: C R Neelakandan |date=2018-09-13 |website=News Experts |language=en-US |access-date=2018-11-07}}</ref>\n\nNeelakandan is married to [[V. M. Girija]], a poet and staff of the [[All India Radio]], Kochi. The couple has two daughters, Aardra and Aarcha and the family lives in [[Kakkanadu]], in Kochi.<ref name=\"\u0d35\u0d3f \u0d0e\u0d02 \u0d17\u0d3f\u0d30\u0d3f\u0d1c\">{{Cite web |url=http://ml.sayahna.org/index.php/%E0%B4%B5%E0%B4%BF_%E0%B4%8E%E0%B4%82_%E0%B4%97%E0%B4%BF%E0%B4%B0%E0%B4%BF%E0%B4%9C |title=\u0d35\u0d3f \u0d0e\u0d02 \u0d17\u0d3f\u0d30\u0d3f\u0d1c |date=2018-11-06 |website=Sayahna |access-date=2018-11-06}}</ref>\n\n==Books==\n* ''Paristhithiyum Aagolavalkaranavum'' (Environment and Globalisation)\n* ''Prakrthiyude Nilavilikal''\n* ''Lavlin, Rekhakaliloode''<ref name=\"\u0d32\u0d3e\u0d35\u0d4d\u200c\u0d32\u0d3f\u0d28\u0d4d\u200d \u0d30\u0d47\u0d16\u0d15\u0d33\u0d3f\u0d32\u0d42\u0d1f\u0d46 \">{{Cite web |url=https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/14168984.C_R_Neelakandan |title=\u0d32\u0d3e\u0d35\u0d4d\u200c\u0d32\u0d3f\u0d28\u0d4d\u200d \u0d30\u0d47\u0d16\u0d15\u0d33\u0d3f\u0d32\u0d42\u0d1f\u0d46  |last=C.R. Neelakandan |date=2018-11-07 |website=www.goodreads.com |access-date=2018-11-07}}</ref>\n* ''Aam adhmi, Sadharanakarante Party''\n* ''Paristhithiyute Varthamanangal''\n* ''Harithavarthamanangal''\n\n==Awards==\n* Baba Award{{citation needed|date=March 2017}}\n* Mukundan C. Menon award{{citation needed|date=March 2017}}\n* A. Sujanapal Award{{citation needed|date=March 2017}}\n* First Oorja Kerala Award{{citation needed|date=March 2017}}\n* Evoorath Award etc.{{citation needed|date=March 2017}}\n\n==Amnesty International==\nIn 2016, he supported [[Amnesty international]] in the controversy against [[Akhil Bharatiya Vidyarthi Parishad|ABVP]].<ref>http://www.bangalorewishesh.com/378-news-headlines/41220-anti-national-slogans-at-amnesty-international-meet.html</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{Cite web |url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/nation/politics/190416/aam-admi-party-not-to-fight-set-to-defeat-tainted.html |title=Aam Admi Party not to fight, set to defeat tainted |date=2016-04-19 |website=Deccan Chronicle |language=en |access-date=2018-11-07}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20100523035857/http://www.mathrubhumi.com/english/news.php?id=91967 Mathrubhumi, News of attack]\n*{{YouTube|julV30X7oJg|Neelakantan's allegation against Nuclear establishment}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Neelakandan, C. R.}}\n[[Category:Malayali people]]\n[[Category:1957 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Indian environmental writers]]\n[[Category:Activists from Kerala]]\n[[Category:Aam Aadmi Party politicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian politicians]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Thrissur]]\n[[Category:Malayalam-language writers]]\n[[Category:Writers from Thrissur]]\n[[Category:Indian anti-globalization activists]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian writers]]\n[[Category:Indian political writers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2016}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=August 2016}}\n\n'''C. R. Neelakandan''' is an Indian environmental activist, politician and writer.<ref name=\"Social workers urged to work for the voiceless people\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-kerala/social-workers-urged-to-work-for-the-voiceless-people/article3086056.ece |title=Social workers urged to work for the voiceless people |date=2006-08-06 |website=The Hindu |language=en-IN |access-date=2018-11-07}}</ref> A a regular contributor to Malayalam periodicals on environmental issues, Neelakandan is the State Convener of [[Aam Aadmi Party]] Kerala since 3 January 2016.<ref name=\"CR Neelakandan \u2013 Aam Aadmi Party\">{{Cite web |url=http://kerala.aamaadmiparty.org/teams/cr-neelakandan/ |title=CR Neelakandan \u2013 Aam Aadmi Party |website=kerala.aamaadmiparty.org |language=en-US |access-date=2018-11-07}}</ref>\n\n== Biography ==\nNeelakandan born to C.P Raman Namboothiri and Savithri Antharjanam on 1957 at karuvannoor in Thrissur District, Kerala. He completed his education from Christ College Irinjalakkuda and [[Government Engineering College, Thrissur]]. He was an activist of [[Students' Federation of India|SFI]] at district and state level while studying. After his study he went on training from [[Bhabha Atomic Research Centre]] Bombay. He joined [[Keltron]] in 1981 and was the Deputy General Manager of Keltron in its Aroor branch and retired in May 2015.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.mathrubhumi.com/english/news.php?id=20823&cat=1&sub=14&subit=0 |title=Mathrubhumi - Keltron relocates CR Neelakandan |access-date=4 June 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120910045216/http://www.mathrubhumi.com/english/news.php?id=20823&cat=1&sub=14&subit=0 |archive-date=10 September 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nHe Began his political activism in students movement, he was arrested during [[The Emergency (India)|The Emergency]] and was held in illegal custody for alleged possession of communist literature. Later he joined SFI, and also worked in the Communist Party. In 2014, he joined the Aam Admi Party and became a member of the State Executive Committee. He actively participates in environmental issues such as public protest against waste dumping at various places across the state such as Lalur, Vilappilashala, Panamkuttichira, Brahmapuram, Pettippalam etc, Struggles like [[Silent Valley National Park|Silent Valley]], National Highway Protection Samithy, Chengara, [[Plachimada]], GAIUL Pipe Line, High Speed Rail Corridor, Many mining projects like Mineral sand mining on Arattupuzha Coast, Moolampilly displacement, Malabar Gold pollution, Periyar River Protection, [[Endosulfan]] in [[Kazaragod]], Aranmula Airport, Athirappilly and Pooyamkutty HEPs and many others.<ref name=\"\u0d2a\u0d4a\u0d2e\u0d4d\u0d2a\u0d3f\u0d33\u0d48 \u0d12\u0d30\u0d41\u0d2e\u0d48 \u0d2a\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d35\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d15\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d4d \u0d2a\u0d3f\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d41\u0d23: \u0d38\u0d3f.\u0d06\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d \u0d28\u0d40\u0d32\u0d15\u0d23\u0d4d\u0d20\u0d28\u0d4d\u200d  \u0d28\u0d3f\u0d30\u0d3e\u0d39\u0d3e\u0d30 \u0d38\u0d2e\u0d30\u0d02 \u0d24\u0d41\u0d1f\u0d19\u0d4d\u0d19\u0d3f\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.mathrubhumi.com/tv/ReadMore/34424/cr/E |title=\u0d2a\u0d4a\u0d2e\u0d4d\u0d2a\u0d3f\u0d33\u0d48 \u0d12\u0d30\u0d41\u0d2e\u0d48 \u0d2a\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d35\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d15\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d4d \u0d2a\u0d3f\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d41\u0d23: \u0d38\u0d3f.\u0d06\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d \u0d28\u0d40\u0d32\u0d15\u0d23\u0d4d\u0d20\u0d28\u0d4d\u200d  \u0d28\u0d3f\u0d30\u0d3e\u0d39\u0d3e\u0d30 \u0d38\u0d2e\u0d30\u0d02 \u0d24\u0d41\u0d1f\u0d19\u0d4d\u0d19\u0d3f |date=2018-11-07 |website=www.mathrubhumi.com |language=en |access-date=2018-11-07}}</ref><ref name=\"Making a Show: The Black Money Bill\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.epw.in/author/c-r-neelakandan |title=Making a Show: The Black Money Bill |date=2015-06-05 |website=Economic and Political Weekly |language=en |access-date=2018-11-07}}</ref><ref name=\"Govt Denying Freedom of Speech: C R Neelakandan\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.newsexperts.in/govt-denying-freedom-speech-c-r-neelakandam/ |title=Govt Denying Freedom of Speech: C R Neelakandan |date=2018-09-13 |website=News Experts |language=en-US |access-date=2018-11-07}}</ref>\n\nNeelakandan is married to [[V. M. Girija]], a poet and staff of the [[All India Radio]], Kochi. The couple has two daughters, Aardra and Aarcha and the family lives in [[Kakkanadu]], in Kochi.<ref name=\"\u0d35\u0d3f \u0d0e\u0d02 \u0d17\u0d3f\u0d30\u0d3f\u0d1c\">{{Cite web |url=http://ml.sayahna.org/index.php/%E0%B4%B5%E0%B4%BF_%E0%B4%8E%E0%B4%82_%E0%B4%97%E0%B4%BF%E0%B4%B0%E0%B4%BF%E0%B4%9C |title=\u0d35\u0d3f \u0d0e\u0d02 \u0d17\u0d3f\u0d30\u0d3f\u0d1c |date=2018-11-06 |website=Sayahna |access-date=2018-11-06}}</ref>\n\n==Books==\n* ''Paristhithiyum Aagolavalkaranavum'' (Environment and Globalisation)\n* ''Prakrthiyude Nilavilikal''\n* ''Lavlin, Rekhakaliloode''<ref name=\"\u0d32\u0d3e\u0d35\u0d4d\u200c\u0d32\u0d3f\u0d28\u0d4d\u200d \u0d30\u0d47\u0d16\u0d15\u0d33\u0d3f\u0d32\u0d42\u0d1f\u0d46 \">{{Cite web |url=https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/14168984.C_R_Neelakandan |title=\u0d32\u0d3e\u0d35\u0d4d\u200c\u0d32\u0d3f\u0d28\u0d4d\u200d \u0d30\u0d47\u0d16\u0d15\u0d33\u0d3f\u0d32\u0d42\u0d1f\u0d46  |last=C.R. Neelakandan |date=2018-11-07 |website=www.goodreads.com |access-date=2018-11-07}}</ref>\n* ''Aam adhmi, Sadharanakarante Party''\n* ''Paristhithiyute Varthamanangal''\n* ''Harithavarthamanangal''\n\n==Awards==\n* Baba Award{{citation needed|date=March 2017}}\n* Mukundan C. Menon award{{citation needed|date=March 2017}}\n* A. Sujanapal Award{{citation needed|date=March 2017}}\n* First Oorja Kerala Award{{citation needed|date=March 2017}}\n* Evoorath Award etc.{{citation needed|date=March 2017}}\n==Amnesty International==\nIn 2016, he supported [[Amnesty international]] in the controversy against [[Akhil Bharatiya Vidyarthi Parishad|ABVP]].<ref>http://www.bangalorewishesh.com/378-news-headlines/41220-anti-national-slogans-at-amnesty-international-meet.html</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{Cite web |url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/nation/politics/190416/aam-admi-party-not-to-fight-set-to-defeat-tainted.html |title=Aam Admi Party not to fight, set to defeat tainted |date=2016-04-19 |website=Deccan Chronicle |language=en |access-date=2018-11-07}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20100523035857/http://www.mathrubhumi.